&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Community 0-19 Service&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Specialist Community Public Health Nurse (School Nurse)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Ref No: A-20-45263&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Band 6 (2 posts available)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Full Time 37.5 hours/ Part Time 30 hours &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Location: Sheffield&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Salary – Band 6: &lt;/span&gt;£&lt;span&gt;31,365- £37,890&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Sheffield Children’s’ NHS Foundation Trust currently has vacancies for both a full time and a part time 30 hrs per week , Specialist Community Public Health Nurse, (School Nurse), within the 0 – 19 service. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking for enthusiastic, highly motivated, innovative School Nurses with a flexible approach to join the dynamic and forward thinking 0-19 Service in Sheffield.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The 0-19 (School Nurse component) Service in Sheffield is committed to delivering high quality care to children 5-19 years and their families. Our delivery model for Children and Young People’s Service (0-19) is based on the Healthy Child Programme and the delivery of the Sheffield School Based Immunisation Programme..&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Early identification, intervention and prevention are key elements of our delivery. This is an opportunity for individuals who are committed to partnership working and who are able to demonstrate a willingness to adapt to new ways of working to effectively deliver the healthy child programme to children, young people and their families.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The School Nursing Service is based in various locations across the city and their work is city wide.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Applications are welcome from experienced and newly qualified School Nurses.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For further information and an informal discussion please contact Delya Lane, NCMP lead on 07824 384694&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
